    title: "Knoxville Hosted a World's Fair Nobody Remembers",
    summary: "In 1982, Knoxville hosted a World's Fair that drew 11 million visitors. The Sunsphere, a 266-foot tower topped with a gold glass ball, still stands as a monument to the event everyone forgot.",
    fullText: "The 1982 World's Fair in Knoxville, Tennessee was themed around energy and drew over 11 million visitors during its six-month run. The fair's most visible legacy is the Sunsphere, a 266-foot steel tower topped with a 75-foot gold-mirrored glass sphere that dominates the Knoxville skyline. The fair was a financial disappointment, failing to meet attendance projections, and it has been largely forgotten by history. The Simpsons mocked it in a 1996 episode where Bart discovers the Sunsphere is used to store unsold wigs. In reality, the Sunsphere sat empty for years before being renovated and reopened with an observation deck and event space. Knoxville itself is a gateway to the Great Smoky Mountains, the most-visited national park in America with over 12 million visitors per year. The Sunsphere remains a beloved if slightly embarrassing civic landmark.",
