    title: "The Rock Nobody Could Escape (Except Maybe Three Guys)",
    summary: "Alcatraz Federal Penitentiary held America's most dangerous criminals on a rock in San Francisco Bay. In 1962, three men escaped using dummy heads made of soap and real hair. They were never found.",
    fullText: "Alcatraz Federal Penitentiary operated from 1934 to 1963 on a rocky island in San Francisco Bay, holding inmates considered too dangerous or escape-prone for other prisons. Famous inmates included Al Capone, Machine Gun Kelly, and Robert Stroud, the Birdman of Alcatraz. The prison boasted it was inescapable: the 1.25-mile swim to shore through frigid, shark-frequented, current-swept water was considered impossible. In June 1962, Frank Morris and brothers John and Clarence Anglin chipped through the ventilation grates in their cells using sharpened spoons, climbed through utility corridors, and launched a raft made of raincoats into the bay. They left dummy heads made of soap, toilet paper, and real human hair in their beds. Their bodies were never found, and the FBI officially presumed them dead. However, a 2013 letter allegedly from John Anglin claimed they survived. The case remains open.",
